ust his leadership as you would mine.  He was hosting planes raids a good month or two before I gave my first shot at Fear.<br><br>****<br>This raid is open signup, but I will be giving preference to LCG members, friends, and those who have raided with me in the past.  Port up time is 9 pm EST, so please be there by 8:30 so I can include you in groups.<br><br>Loot rules: Everyone who can use an armor piece is entitled to roll.  Once you win something you are out until everyone of your class has won something.  Weapons, wands, and stuff like that does not count against armor drops.<br><br>Epic loot rules: I am reserving any ranger hate stones that drop for LCG rangers.  Essense of a Vampire if it drops may be rolled on by myself and up to _1_ other enchanter... who must be level 54 or higher.  Other epic drops are not currently defaulted.<br><br>SPECIAL NOTE:  This raid is good for classes for the most part.  Could use another shaman or two, and maybe an experienced monk for pulling.  But should be gtg.<br><br>***<br><br>Standard raid rules apply...<br><br>1. Show up 30 minutes ahead of time.  THIS IS REQUIRED! Hate takes a long time to set up and as this is a weeknight people won't be able to stay up all night... so 6 pm PST (9 pm EST) is when we start porting up.  Period.  (If you are on the roster I will give a standby your spot if you are not there at 5:30.)<br><br>2. If you have specific group requests, let me know ahead of time. After I announce groups is too late.<br><br>3. Everyone who can use an armor drop is entitled to roll for it. I personally am not a big fan of 2 piece rules. Asking someone to roll on inferior items to what they have so that they can later have a better shot at a better, different item, is... stupid.<br><br>4. Everyone is required to make an /assist &lt;primary tank's name&gt; hotkey as well as an /assist &lt;secondary tank's name&gt; hotkey.<br><br>5. You may chat during the raid in ooc. You may not chat in shout. Shout is only to be used by the group leaders, the raid leader, the pull team, and raid enchanters.<br><br>7. Dropable loot will be held until the end of the raid and then distributed on a need before greed basis. Money items and gems will be used 1st to pay the cost of peridots. Any remaining will be distributed among those who won nothing.<br><br>8. There is to be no complaining during the raid that could cause offense to others. You may make joking comments about how tired you are, how sore your fingers are from all the typing, how repetitious your job is (clarity, med, haste, med... rinse repeat) etc. If people complain about how their time is being wasted, or how they didn't win an item, or things of that nature I will have them translocated out and likely will not include them on my future raids. I have seen raids hurl themselves against a seeming impossible barrier get smashed multiple times, and then try again and succeed because of good attitudes. I have seen raids crumble after a single failure due to bad attitudes spread by one or two complainers. (These were open raids, not any LCG raids I have been on.)<br><br>9. We will be using the northern route to camp.<br><br>10. If you somehow get seperated from the raid body... stay where you are and get a loc. Do not guess which way we may have went. Its easier for us to find you just by backtracking than by guessing which way you may have gone.<br><br>11. Do not train the raid. If you get aggroed away from the raid body and are not the puller then fight there, get a loc, and die if necessary. We will get your body and rez you. We would rather not have to get everyone's body and have to rez everyone.<br><br>12. Do not attack before the main assist calls for it. This can occassionally result in trains that wipeout the raid!<br><br>13. Have fun<br><br>14. Have fun!<br><br>15. Have fun!! <br><br><br><br>***<br><br>Currently signed up (This is NOT a roster, this is just to let _me_ more eas